1
00:00:20,911 --> 00:00:23,958
Interviewer: Didn’t you ask him on
the way where he was taking you?

2
00:00:23,983 --> 00:00:26,432
I asked him where he was taking me, and
he told me he was taking me to the judge

3
00:00:29,297 --> 00:00:31,536
To their own judge

4
00:00:32,656 --> 00:00:34,766
He took me to the
investigative judge there

5
00:00:35,755 --> 00:00:40,026
He looked at my slip and said,
You’re so-and-so. I said, Yes

6
00:00:40,703 --> 00:00:42,604
He said, Take him for flogging

7
00:00:44,954 --> 00:00:47,948
So they brought me
into that last room inside

8
00:00:49,094 --> 00:00:50,370
There’s a room there

9
00:00:51,151 --> 00:00:52,922
They flogged me in that room

10
00:00:53,912 --> 00:00:55,032
Interviewer: The same room?

11
00:00:55,057 --> 00:00:56,646
No, that room over there

12
00:00:57,558 --> 00:00:58,860
That room inside, over there

13
00:00:59,172 --> 00:01:01,568
Interviewer: Where
did you go in from here?

14
00:01:01,593 --> 00:01:03,964
He took me up these
stairs and into the room

15
00:01:11,724 --> 00:01:13,286
Interviewer: When you
came down, what did you see?

16
00:01:13,311 --> 00:01:16,178
You were a prisoner
for one day in that room?

17
00:01:17,532 --> 00:01:21,151
I also saw ISIS members
and other people there

18
00:01:21,594 --> 00:01:25,058
Some were being released

19
00:01:25,568 --> 00:01:27,469
And others were
being brought in here

20
00:01:28,355 --> 00:01:31,115
On light and heavy
charges and sentences

21
00:01:31,662 --> 00:01:33,875
They brought them in

22
00:01:38,641 --> 00:01:40,047
Interviewer: Did you know
how many lashes you would get?

23
00:01:40,072 --> 00:01:41,271
I didn’t know exactly

24
00:01:41,922 --> 00:01:45,073
But I heard the judge sentence
me to one hundred lashes

25
00:01:45,098 --> 00:01:47,443
The day before, when they took my
belongings, he said, One hundred lashes

26
00:01:47,808 --> 00:01:49,292
He told me, You have
one hundred lashes

27
00:01:49,865 --> 00:01:51,506
But go now to be disciplined

28
00:01:52,053 --> 00:01:54,266
Go into the prison;
God is generous

29
00:01:54,917 --> 00:01:56,245
Until tomorrow, God is generous

30
00:01:56,844 --> 00:01:58,797
At ten in the morning
they brought me

31
00:02:00,334 --> 00:02:02,782
They took me to the judge,
and he said, Take him for flogging

32
00:02:03,901 --> 00:02:06,115
They took me into the
last room and flogged me

33
00:02:07,719 --> 00:02:09,047
Interviewer: How many
lashes did they give you?

34
00:02:09,072 --> 00:02:10,323
They flogged me
one hundred lashes

35
00:02:13,865 --> 00:02:17,563
Interviewer: From where did the ISIS member take
you out when you left the investigation room?

36
00:02:17,588 --> 00:02:20,219
He didn’t take me out from there;
he took me out via these stairs

37
00:02:20,870 --> 00:02:22,250
Interviewer: Could you
take us to the room?

38
00:02:22,275 --> 00:02:23,161
Sure

39
00:03:02,016 --> 00:03:03,448
He didn’t take me out from here

40
00:03:04,230 --> 00:03:07,224
He didn’t take me up these
stairs, but those stairs over there

41
00:03:14,282 --> 00:03:17,953
Interviewer: What did you say to
him when he brought you here?

42
00:03:17,978 --> 00:03:19,646
I didn’t talk to him

43
00:03:19,671 --> 00:03:22,954
He held me by the hand and
brought me to the flogger who was here

44
00:03:23,813 --> 00:03:25,297
I was flogged in this room

45
00:03:27,042 --> 00:03:28,422
Interviewer: Didn’t you talk
while that was happening?

46
00:03:28,447 --> 00:03:29,803
I didn’t talk

47
00:03:29,828 --> 00:03:33,006
He told me, You’ll be flogged.
I said, I’ll be flogged, OK

48
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:35,160
Will I die from flogging?!

49
00:03:35,889 --> 00:03:38,649
Interviewer: What did you
see in this room and that room?

50
00:03:38,674 --> 00:03:43,519
ISIS members were
present in this room

51
00:03:45,420 --> 00:03:46,748
In these rooms too

52
00:03:46,773 --> 00:03:50,420
ISIS is here in great numbers

53
00:03:50,759 --> 00:03:52,660
This is their prison

54
00:03:53,467 --> 00:03:54,326
Headquarters

55
00:03:59,248 --> 00:04:01,696
Interviewer: Were there people
waiting for their turn to be flogged?

56
00:04:02,451 --> 00:04:03,571
No, there were not

57
00:04:04,457 --> 00:04:07,998
They only bring the prisoner when he is sentenced
to flogging. No one waits for the other to finish

58
00:04:08,597 --> 00:04:11,826
And when he said, 100 lashes,
he brought me to this place

59
00:04:12,451 --> 00:04:14,014
The flogger took me inside

60
00:04:15,096 --> 00:04:17,336
There is a flogger
specialized for these matters

61
00:04:18,534 --> 00:04:20,669
He came with his whip
and flogged me 100 lashes

62
00:04:22,674 --> 00:04:24,367
But at first the
lashes were light

63
00:04:25,070 --> 00:04:26,164
He was counting them that way

64
00:04:27,310 --> 00:04:32,622
Then he kept going, harder each
time, and flogged me very hard in the end

65
00:04:33,325 --> 00:04:35,747
So it would show that the
prisoner had been flogged

66
00:04:36,659 --> 00:04:40,148
Because if the judge sees your
back and it is not properly flogged

67
00:04:40,539 --> 00:04:42,518
He orders that you
be flogged again

68
00:04:43,664 --> 00:04:45,070
Saying your flogging was light

69
00:04:45,747 --> 00:04:47,154
Meaning it was not strong

70
00:04:48,846 --> 00:04:50,279
Meaning it depends on the lashes

71
00:04:50,304 --> 00:04:54,081
If it is 50 or 60 lashes, they
are light and not very strong

72
00:04:54,706 --> 00:04:56,763
After that the remaining
lashes have to be severe
